16/02/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Visiting Zagreb on Wednesday (15 February), European Commission President Jose Manuel Barroso praised Croatia's progress in the EU accession process, saying the country is on the right track.
Accompanied by EU Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn, Barroso is visiting several capitals in the region.
He reaffirmed that Croatia has real prospects for EU membership and urged a continued commitment to implementing reforms.
Also Wednesday, Bosnia and Herzegovina Prime Minister Adnan Terzic paid a daylong visit to Zagreb.
He and Croatian counterpart Ivo Sanader agreed to establish an inter-governmental working group to tackle the thorniest bilateral issues -- particularly, those involving border and territorial disputes.
(Novi list, Nezavisne novine, Dnevni avaz - 16/02/06;
HINA, HRT - 15/02/06)
